 kamma is a principle of justice at work in the universe; it tells us that every action or intention has an inevitable result, it tells us all actions has either good or bad results and the actions with good results leads to merit while those with bad results lead to punishment 
 the Four Holy Truths, is a statement of Buddhist ethical teachings. It presents the Middle Way as, indeed, a way or a path along which one 
progresses through one or several lives until enlightenment is finally reached. one need to know the right path to follow in order to be sure of the actions that will lead to merits. Through the Sermon on the Four Holy Truths, we learn that in Buddhism, religious and ethical teachings are one and the 
same: What the Buddha taught was the ethical path that, for him and for his followers, leads to enlightenment.this ent
 
 
